1
00:00:14,467 --> 00:00:17,967
Yen, did you already forget
our moments together?

2
00:00:18,033 --> 00:00:20,500
I was happy being with you
on the island.

3
00:00:20,567 --> 00:00:22,567
But maybe that's all
we can have.

4
00:00:22,633 --> 00:00:25,300
You're hurting because
you're in love with him.

5
00:00:25,367 --> 00:00:30,600
I would choose to get hurt
than hurt someone else.

6
00:00:30,667 --> 00:00:33,600
If you want a free lawyer,
you should go to PAO.

7
00:00:33,700 --> 00:00:36,933
And they only accept
defense cases.

8
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:38,633
PAO will not accept your case

9
00:00:38,700 --> 00:00:40,167
because you're the one
filing a lawsuit.

10
00:00:40,233 --> 00:00:42,133
I saw the way you looked at her
earlier.

11
00:00:42,200 --> 00:00:43,700
You never looked at me
like that.

12
00:00:43,767 --> 00:00:46,300
So are you going to tell me
you like her more?

13
00:00:46,367 --> 00:00:48,000
What if I say yes?

14
00:00:48,067 --> 00:00:49,067
No way!

15
00:00:49,133 --> 00:00:50,067
The nerve of that woman!

16
00:00:50,133 --> 00:00:51,800
How is she going to sue me?

17
00:00:51,867 --> 00:00:53,167
She doesn't have money.

18
00:00:53,233 --> 00:00:55,633
Just be grateful
she has no money.

19
00:00:55,700 --> 00:00:56,833
Because if she does,

20
00:00:56,900 --> 00:00:58,500
my reputation will be
on the line.

21
00:00:58,567 --> 00:01:01,167
It's so hard to be poor.

22
00:01:01,233 --> 00:01:02,433
She's right.

23
00:01:02,500 --> 00:01:06,033
My case will just get dismissed.

24
00:01:06,100 --> 00:01:07,800
I thought you would stay away
from Red.

25
00:01:07,900 --> 00:01:10,200
But it seems like you're
making him more confused.

26
00:01:10,267 --> 00:01:11,633
Sabina, I don't have any
intention

27
00:01:11,700 --> 00:01:13,200
to ruin your relationship.

28
00:01:13,267 --> 00:01:15,733
I'm already avoiding him. What
else do you want me to do?

29
00:01:15,800 --> 00:01:17,433
Oh, my God! Help me!

30
00:01:17,500 --> 00:01:18,900
Help me!

31
00:01:18,967 --> 00:01:20,067
Help!

32
00:01:20,133 --> 00:01:21,533
- Raichu!
- Red!

33
00:01:21,600 --> 00:01:23,600
Help!

34
00:01:23,667 --> 00:01:24,867
Oh, my God, help us!

35
00:01:24,933 --> 00:01:25,867
- Please, help me!
- Yen!

36
00:01:25,933 --> 00:01:27,167
Sab!

37
00:01:28,767 --> 00:01:29,533
Help me!

38
00:01:29,600 --> 00:01:31,500
Raichu!

39
00:01:31,567 --> 00:01:32,500
Raichu!

40
00:01:32,567 --> 00:01:33,667
Hold on.

41
00:01:35,767 --> 00:01:37,933
- Raichu, help!
- Hurry up!

42
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:40,400
I don't want to die here!
Hurry up!

43
00:01:40,500 --> 00:01:41,800
Come on, Red!

44
00:01:41,867 --> 00:01:43,300
Red, please!

45
00:01:43,367 --> 00:01:44,767
- Help!
- Wait.

46
00:01:44,833 --> 00:01:45,967
Just hold on.

47
00:01:47,400 --> 00:01:49,667
Oh, my God.
Help me, please.

48
00:01:49,733 --> 00:01:50,867
Please, help me, Red.

49
00:01:50,933 --> 00:01:53,100
Raichu, help me!

50
00:01:53,167 --> 00:01:55,933
Raichu, help!
Raichu!

51
00:01:56,000 --> 00:01:57,567
- I'm on it!
- Red, please.

52
00:01:57,633 --> 00:01:58,633
Please, help me, Red.

53
00:01:58,700 --> 00:02:00,033
Red, I'm begging you.

54
00:02:00,100 --> 00:02:01,200
Red, help me, please.

55
00:02:01,267 --> 00:02:02,600
I don't want to die,
I don't want to die.

56
00:02:02,667 --> 00:02:04,767
Raichu!

57
00:02:04,833 --> 00:02:07,267
Yen, grab my hand.

58
00:02:07,333 --> 00:02:08,700
What?

59
00:02:08,767 --> 00:02:10,167
Come on, let's see
the village chief.

60
00:02:10,233 --> 00:02:12,333
- Yeah, let's do that!
- Go ahead!

61
00:02:12,400 --> 00:02:14,367
What you're doing is unlawful!

62
00:02:14,467 --> 00:02:15,800
Go!

63
00:02:15,867 --> 00:02:17,333
How dare you!

64
00:02:19,300 --> 00:02:20,567
Gossipers!

65
00:02:22,300 --> 00:02:24,267
I wonder who told them.

66
00:02:24,333 --> 00:02:26,200
We don't know anyone here.

67
00:02:26,267 --> 00:02:28,967
Unless there's a rat
who told them.

68
00:02:33,200 --> 00:02:34,500
You mean Rina?

69
00:02:34,567 --> 00:02:36,367
She's the only one
who would do this.

70
00:02:38,333 --> 00:02:40,233
Just ignore them.

71
00:02:40,300 --> 00:02:41,833
And we're not going to leave.

72
00:02:41,900 --> 00:02:44,000
My God, I paid two months
in advance.

73
00:02:44,067 --> 00:02:46,133
They can't shoo us away
just like that.

74
00:02:46,200 --> 00:02:47,467
The nerve of those people!

75
00:02:47,567 --> 00:02:48,933
They ruined our day!

76
00:02:53,033 --> 00:02:54,333
Is that Rina?

77
00:02:55,767 --> 00:02:58,333
What are you doing?
You should save me first!

78
00:02:58,400 --> 00:02:59,500
Stay still!

79
00:02:59,567 --> 00:03:01,300
I'll save you too.
Just wait.

80
00:03:01,367 --> 00:03:03,500
Yen, hold on to me.

81
00:03:03,567 --> 00:03:04,967
Come on!

82
00:03:05,033 --> 00:03:06,567
I'm going to die here, Red.

83
00:03:06,633 --> 00:03:08,600
Please! Don't leave me!

84
00:03:08,667 --> 00:03:10,033
Don't leave me!

85
00:03:10,100 --> 00:03:12,133
Yenyen, don't!

86
00:03:12,200 --> 00:03:13,433
Stay here!

87
00:03:13,500 --> 00:03:16,833
Help me! Don't leave me!

88
00:03:16,900 --> 00:03:19,200
Don't leave me, Red, please!

89
00:03:19,267 --> 00:03:20,533
- Please, help.
- Sab.

90
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:22,567
- Help me!
- Sab, grab my hand.

91
00:03:22,667 --> 00:03:23,800
Come on!

92
00:03:36,333 --> 00:03:37,900
Get up, Sabina.

93
00:03:38,967 --> 00:03:40,867
Red, Red.

94
00:03:42,567 --> 00:03:44,900
It hurts. My leg hurts.

95
00:03:44,967 --> 00:03:47,200
I can't move.
I can't move my legs.

96
00:03:47,267 --> 00:03:48,867
- I can't move it.
- Are you okay, Sab?

97
00:03:48,933 --> 00:03:50,600
Let go of me! It hurts.

98
00:03:50,667 --> 00:03:52,733
- Wait.
- Eden!

99
00:03:52,800 --> 00:03:55,333
Sab, what happened to you?

100
00:03:55,433 --> 00:03:58,033
- Are you okay?
- Help me, please.

101
00:04:03,967 --> 00:04:05,000
I really can't...

102
00:04:05,067 --> 00:04:07,267
bring me to the shelter, please.

103
00:04:07,333 --> 00:04:08,700
Please.

104
00:04:08,767 --> 00:04:12,067
- Sabina, let me help you.
- Hold on to me.

105
00:04:12,133 --> 00:04:14,533
- Slowly.
- Let Red do it.

106
00:04:14,600 --> 00:04:17,533
- It's fine.
- No. You need help.

107
00:04:17,600 --> 00:04:18,800
Come here.

108
00:04:20,400 --> 00:04:22,433
- Let's go.
- You can't walk anymore.

109
00:04:25,300 --> 00:04:26,867
- Hey, Rina!
- Amanda!

110
00:04:26,933 --> 00:04:28,333
Amanda.

111
00:04:28,433 --> 00:04:30,667
I knew it was you.

112
00:04:31,567 --> 00:04:33,100
Get off the car.

113
00:04:33,167 --> 00:04:34,633
- Talk to me.
- Amanda...

114
00:04:34,700 --> 00:04:36,967
Get off the car! Talk to me.

115
00:04:37,033 --> 00:04:38,800
Why? What's wrong?

116
00:04:38,867 --> 00:04:40,500
You're the wrong one.
You're evil.

117
00:04:40,567 --> 00:04:42,967
- I'm just telling the truth.
- Oh, really?

118
00:04:43,033 --> 00:04:45,067
And besides, I am doing
a charity here.

119
00:04:45,133 --> 00:04:46,200
Careful, you might get burned.

120
00:04:46,267 --> 00:04:48,567
I'm concerned about
the residents here.

121
00:04:48,633 --> 00:04:50,767
Especially about the mothers
like me...

122
00:04:50,833 --> 00:04:52,567
Who are worthless.

123
00:04:52,633 --> 00:04:57,267
You might take their children
as your next victim.

124
00:04:57,333 --> 00:04:58,567
That's it.

125
00:04:58,633 --> 00:05:00,533
I am simply concerned.

126
00:05:00,600 --> 00:05:04,800
And yes, life is unfair, Amanda.

127
00:05:04,900 --> 00:05:09,033
I realized that when my son died
because of you.

128
00:05:09,867 --> 00:05:11,733
Life is unfair.

129
00:05:12,667 --> 00:05:15,367
But right now,
I have the upper hand.

130
00:05:16,600 --> 00:05:18,933
You are helpless because
you have no money.

131
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:20,233
You can't even file
a case against me.

132
00:05:20,300 --> 00:05:24,400
You can't get even
because you are helpless.

133
00:05:24,467 --> 00:05:30,633
That's what I felt when my
son died because of you.

134
00:05:30,700 --> 00:05:33,700
I felt so cheated.

135
00:05:33,800 --> 00:05:35,567
That's what I will
make you feel.

136
00:05:37,100 --> 00:05:40,267
How does it feel to be cheated?

137
00:05:41,333 --> 00:05:42,767
To be tricked?

138
00:05:45,267 --> 00:05:46,500
Let's go, Zandro.

139
00:05:46,567 --> 00:05:48,267
The stench of this place
makes me feel like throwing up.

140
00:05:48,333 --> 00:05:49,267
Why do you keep
coming back here?

141
00:05:49,333 --> 00:05:50,800
You smell bad!

142
00:05:50,867 --> 00:05:53,033
- Come on! Fight me!
- Why don't you leave?

143
00:05:53,100 --> 00:05:54,867
I won't give you the pleasure.
You stink!

144
00:05:54,933 --> 00:05:56,500
Take a bath first!

145
00:05:56,567 --> 00:05:58,000
- Let's go, Zandro!
- It's your own smell!

146
00:05:58,067 --> 00:06:00,233
Take a bath first!

147
00:06:01,233 --> 00:06:02,267
Go on, leave!

148
00:06:02,333 --> 00:06:03,300
- Let's go, Zandro!
- Leave!

149
00:06:03,367 --> 00:06:05,100
Get out of here!
Are you not leaving?

150
00:06:05,167 --> 00:06:07,133
- I will break this!
- Leave!

151
00:06:07,200 --> 00:06:09,000
You keep coming back here.

152
00:06:09,100 --> 00:06:10,667
Are you already
in love with me?

153
00:06:10,733 --> 00:06:11,733
You love my smell!

154
00:06:11,800 --> 00:06:13,167
They keep coming back!

155
00:06:15,867 --> 00:06:16,933
Oh my God.

156
00:06:17,900 --> 00:06:19,033
It hurts.

157
00:06:19,100 --> 00:06:20,033
Go on. Sit down.

158
00:06:20,100 --> 00:06:21,433
Ouch.

159
00:06:21,500 --> 00:06:23,333
Oh my God, I really
can't move it.

160
00:06:23,400 --> 00:06:24,767
Oh my gosh.

161
00:06:24,833 --> 00:06:27,600
I think it got stuck
in the quicksand.

162
00:06:27,667 --> 00:06:30,767
I think it made my leg worse.

163
00:06:30,833 --> 00:06:31,867
Oh my God.

164
00:06:31,933 --> 00:06:34,733
I told you to get some rest,
didn't I?

165
00:06:34,800 --> 00:06:36,467
Don't get mad at her.

166
00:06:36,533 --> 00:06:38,633
No one wanted this to happen.

167
00:06:42,400 --> 00:06:44,667
Red, can you please
don't leave me?

168
00:06:44,733 --> 00:06:47,200
I really need you now.

169
00:06:47,267 --> 00:06:49,033
I'll just change my clothes.

170
00:06:55,067 --> 00:06:57,300
I'm so sorry.

171
00:06:57,367 --> 00:06:58,300
Since they're not here,

172
00:06:58,367 --> 00:07:00,867
can you help me
change my clothes?

173
00:07:02,033 --> 00:07:03,167
Please?

174
00:07:06,367 --> 00:07:07,867
I'll just prepare the fish.

175
00:07:07,933 --> 00:07:09,600
Okay.

176
00:07:09,667 --> 00:07:11,400
Where are your clothes?

177
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:14,667
This one.

178
00:07:42,400 --> 00:07:44,233
Eat first. So you'll regain your
strength.

179
00:07:50,900 --> 00:07:51,933
Thank you.

180
00:07:53,333 --> 00:07:55,600
You know what...

181
00:07:55,667 --> 00:07:57,767
you still haven't changed.

182
00:07:58,200 --> 00:08:02,167
You're still one of the
most caring people I know.

183
00:08:04,600 --> 00:08:08,333
I just miss this...

184
00:08:09,067 --> 00:08:12,400
you, taking care of me.

185
00:08:14,267 --> 00:08:15,367
And...

186
00:08:15,433 --> 00:08:18,700
I just hope we'll return
to the way we were before.

187
00:08:20,900 --> 00:08:22,467
Sab...

188
00:08:22,533 --> 00:08:24,600
I thought...

189
00:08:24,667 --> 00:08:29,033
maybe the reason we survived
the plane crash

190
00:08:29,100 --> 00:08:34,300
is to give us a second chance.

191
00:08:35,567 --> 00:08:38,533
Can we not talk about this
for now?

192
00:08:38,600 --> 00:08:42,333
You should rest.

193
00:08:42,400 --> 00:08:43,700
Regain your strength.

194
00:08:45,733 --> 00:08:47,333
Okay.

195
00:08:47,400 --> 00:08:48,567
It's all right.

196
00:09:04,433 --> 00:09:07,933
I made you a hot compress,
Sabina.

197
00:09:08,833 --> 00:09:12,433
Maybe your foot got strained.

198
00:09:12,500 --> 00:09:15,500
My coach used to put
a hot compress on my foot

199
00:09:15,567 --> 00:09:17,067
whenever it hurt.

200
00:09:17,133 --> 00:09:18,900
Here. This might help.

201
00:09:18,967 --> 00:09:20,867
Just hand it to Red.

202
00:09:20,933 --> 00:09:22,700
He knows what to do.

203
00:09:22,767 --> 00:09:24,167
He'll take care of it.

204
00:09:25,100 --> 00:09:28,733
But thanks anyway.

205
00:09:29,867 --> 00:09:31,200
Thank you, Yen.

206
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:51,000
Sorry.

207
00:09:51,067 --> 00:09:52,433
Careful, please.

208
00:10:10,900 --> 00:10:13,400
Finally, we're going to eat!

209
00:10:13,467 --> 00:10:16,133
I'm so sick of Sabina's fruits.

210
00:10:16,200 --> 00:10:17,867
I deserve this.

211
00:10:17,933 --> 00:10:20,267
We deserve this, Eden.

212
00:10:29,667 --> 00:10:30,667
It's okay.

213
00:10:30,733 --> 00:10:31,900
You don't have to eat.

214
00:10:31,967 --> 00:10:34,267
You're already full.

215
00:10:34,367 --> 00:10:37,067
You're full of jealousy.

216
00:10:37,133 --> 00:10:38,400
What?

217
00:10:38,467 --> 00:10:39,733
Nothing.

218
00:10:39,800 --> 00:10:42,200
I said, don't try to deny it.

219
00:10:42,267 --> 00:10:48,233
I know that you're already
having a hard time.

220
00:10:48,300 --> 00:10:51,200
Why are you making it
difficult for yourself?

221
00:10:51,267 --> 00:10:55,133
You're suppressing
your feelings.

222
00:10:55,200 --> 00:10:59,400
It's so clear that Red
likes you.

223
00:11:01,300 --> 00:11:08,300
Eden, do you think I don't feel
the sexual tension?

224
00:11:08,400 --> 00:11:09,767
It's there.

225
00:11:11,533 --> 00:11:15,667
Raichu, you know my answer
to that.

226
00:11:17,600 --> 00:11:20,533
Our situation is so complicated.

227
00:11:21,867 --> 00:11:23,467
I don't want to make it worse.

228
00:11:25,300 --> 00:11:28,967
And I don't want to hurt
other people.

229
00:11:29,333 --> 00:11:32,900
So you're okay with getting
hurt?

230
00:11:33,467 --> 00:11:36,700
I see that you're hurting.

231
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:41,467
It's possible that Sabina's
feeling is unrequited.

232
00:11:41,567 --> 00:11:46,833
And she has no chance to Red,
right?

233
00:11:47,667 --> 00:11:51,500
You know, I understand her.

234
00:11:54,467 --> 00:12:00,367
My mom experienced the same
thing when my father left us.

235
00:12:01,400 --> 00:12:03,900
It wasn't easy.

236
00:12:03,967 --> 00:12:05,300
It was painful.

237
00:12:09,900 --> 00:12:11,333
I was thinking...

238
00:12:13,967 --> 00:12:20,333
was my father happy
when he left us?

239
00:12:25,400 --> 00:12:33,267
And if he was, does it mean
he made the right decision?

240
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:43,800
I think my decision
to avoid Red is right.

241
00:12:45,900 --> 00:12:52,100
But the problem is why I'm
hurting.

242
00:14:29,600 --> 00:14:31,633
Until when will you avoid me?

243
00:14:34,967 --> 00:14:36,600
Because I can't take it anymore.

244
00:14:39,867 --> 00:14:43,767
I tried my best to like Sabina,
but...

245
00:14:46,300 --> 00:14:48,333
it's you I really like.

246
00:14:52,767 --> 00:14:53,933
You know...

247
00:14:56,233 --> 00:14:59,833
I miss the moments we tease
each other...

248
00:15:04,100 --> 00:15:05,867
our playful moments...

249
00:15:07,733 --> 00:15:13,167
the times we're making plans...

250
00:15:13,833 --> 00:15:16,300
our conversations...

251
00:15:19,133 --> 00:15:20,667
under the stars.

252
00:15:25,367 --> 00:15:29,167
Yen, I miss you.

253
00:15:31,167 --> 00:15:32,900
I really miss you.

254
00:16:43,067 --> 00:16:44,833
Let's stop this, Red.

255
00:16:49,833 --> 00:16:53,733
Nothing will happen as long as
Sabina's there.

256
00:16:56,433 --> 00:16:58,100
She's good to me.

257
00:16:59,133 --> 00:17:01,067
I can't hurt her.

258
00:17:07,100 --> 00:17:10,233
Let's not make it hard
for ourselves.

259
00:17:14,500 --> 00:17:15,833
I'm sorry.

260
00:17:50,233 --> 00:17:52,667
Are you all right, Amanda?

261
00:17:54,567 --> 00:17:58,367
Should I stay with you?

262
00:17:58,433 --> 00:18:02,667
That scheming wench might do
something to you again.

263
00:18:03,467 --> 00:18:07,800
No matter what I do,
Rina won't stop pestering me.

264
00:18:07,867 --> 00:18:09,167
I will just pray to God

265
00:18:09,233 --> 00:18:12,867
that one day she'll wake up
so tired

266
00:18:12,933 --> 00:18:14,733
from what she's doing to me.

267
00:18:15,933 --> 00:18:19,433
I'll just keep living
for my daughter.

268
00:18:20,967 --> 00:18:24,067
By the way, I'll go to the
airline's office

269
00:18:24,167 --> 00:18:27,100
after selling these rice cakes.

270
00:18:27,167 --> 00:18:28,600
I'll ask for updates.

271
00:18:29,967 --> 00:18:31,067
Okay.

272
00:18:32,067 --> 00:18:33,867
- I'm done.
- Be safe, okay?

273
00:18:33,933 --> 00:18:34,933
I will.

274
00:18:35,000 --> 00:18:36,367
See you later.

275
00:18:36,667 --> 00:18:37,567
Amanda!

276
00:18:37,633 --> 00:18:39,333
We know everything about you!

277
00:18:39,400 --> 00:18:41,867
And we'll go to the village
chief to report you!

278
00:18:41,933 --> 00:18:44,367
Just leave if you don't want
to embarrass yourself!

279
00:18:44,433 --> 00:18:46,733
Leave, you criminals!

280
00:18:46,800 --> 00:18:49,433
- Get out of here!
- Leave this place!

281
00:18:49,500 --> 00:18:50,700
Get out of that house!

282
00:18:52,533 --> 00:18:54,000
Get out!

283
00:18:56,500 --> 00:18:57,767
Get out of there!

284
00:18:57,833 --> 00:18:59,400
Leave this place!

285
00:18:59,933 --> 00:19:01,500
Amanda, where are you going?

286
00:19:01,567 --> 00:19:03,233
There she is.
She's going downstairs.

287
00:19:03,300 --> 00:19:04,733
Get out of there!

288
00:19:04,800 --> 00:19:06,633
Criminal!

289
00:19:06,700 --> 00:19:08,300
What are these people doing?

290
00:19:08,367 --> 00:19:10,067
Talk to us!

291
00:19:10,133 --> 00:19:11,267
Get out of there!

292
00:19:13,067 --> 00:19:16,567
- Criminal!
- What are you doing?

293
00:19:16,633 --> 00:19:18,500
No! You're criminals!

294
00:19:18,567 --> 00:19:19,967
Hear me out first!

295
00:19:20,033 --> 00:19:22,433
No! Leave this place!

296
00:19:23,000 --> 00:19:24,367
How dare you!

297
00:19:24,433 --> 00:19:26,600
You're the one who should leave!

298
00:19:26,667 --> 00:19:28,567
You're a criminal!

299
00:19:28,667 --> 00:19:30,367
- You must leave!
- Hear me out first!

300
00:19:30,433 --> 00:19:32,600
- No!
- No!

301
00:19:32,667 --> 00:19:33,867
Just leave!

302
00:19:33,933 --> 00:19:36,067
Are you not going to stop?

303
00:19:36,133 --> 00:19:38,267
You're a criminal.
You should leave.

304
00:19:38,333 --> 00:19:41,133
- That's right!
- Leave our place!

305
00:19:41,433 --> 00:19:42,967
You have the nerve to do this!

306
00:19:43,033 --> 00:19:44,700
What you're doing is wrong!

307
00:19:44,767 --> 00:19:46,633
You are criminals!
Leave our place!

308
00:19:46,700 --> 00:19:48,200
Criminals!

309
00:19:48,933 --> 00:19:49,833
Yen.

310
00:19:52,533 --> 00:19:54,300
So your feet are now okay.

311
00:19:57,633 --> 00:19:59,333
When did it become okay?

312
00:20:00,433 --> 00:20:03,500
Or did it never hurt?

313
00:20:03,600 --> 00:20:05,033
Oh no, no.

314
00:20:05,100 --> 00:20:07,800
Yenyen, let me explain.

315
00:20:07,867 --> 00:20:09,533
No. You don't have to, Sabina.

316
00:20:09,600 --> 00:20:11,433
I already know the truth.

317
00:20:11,500 --> 00:20:13,433
Why are you lying?

318
00:20:14,267 --> 00:20:17,333
Why do you pretend to be sick
in front of Red?

319
00:20:17,400 --> 00:20:19,033
Yenyen...

320
00:20:24,367 --> 00:20:25,900
I won't do anything against you.

321
00:20:25,967 --> 00:20:28,967
The Lord once said, when someone
throws a stone at you...

322
00:20:29,033 --> 00:20:30,933
Oh, please. Don't use God!

323
00:20:32,500 --> 00:20:34,833
Get out of here!

324
00:20:34,900 --> 00:20:37,100
Shove some rice cakes
down her mouth!

325
00:20:38,667 --> 00:20:39,900
Are you sure?

326
00:20:39,967 --> 00:20:40,800
That's good news!

327
00:20:40,867 --> 00:20:41,967
Who was that?

328
00:20:42,033 --> 00:20:43,267
The airlines called.

329
00:20:43,333 --> 00:20:46,667
They said the search and
rescue team found things

330
00:20:46,733 --> 00:20:47,700
on an island.

331
00:20:47,767 --> 00:20:50,133
And they suspect that there
are survivors

332
00:20:50,200 --> 00:20:51,767
on the nearby islands.

333
00:20:51,833 --> 00:20:54,267
I won't let you do
what you want, Sabina!

334
00:20:54,333 --> 00:20:56,200
So, where did they go?

335
00:20:56,267 --> 00:20:57,233
I don't know.

336
00:20:57,300 --> 00:20:58,367
Sab, can't walk.

337
00:20:58,433 --> 00:20:59,867
Her feet are still hurting.

338
00:21:00,733 --> 00:21:02,067
Leave me alone, Sabina!

339
00:21:02,133 --> 00:21:05,333
I won't do that because
you can't see Red!
